BridgeLink
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The images bundle a BridgeLink release binary (downloaded at build time via the
BINARY_URL build argument). BridgeLink is an Innovar Healthcare product derived
from Mirth Connect and is distributed under the Mozilla Public License 2.0.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hardened image base — Docker Hardened Images (Dockerfile.dhi only)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The hardened image (Dockerfile.dhi) is built FROM the Amazon Corretto Debian 13
Docker Hardened Image (DHI):

    dhi.io/amazoncorretto:17-debian13       (runtime)
    dhi.io/amazoncorretto:17-debian13-dev   (build stage)

- Docker's DHI build definitions, patches, and scripts are licensed under the
  Apache License 2.0, which permits building and redistributing derivative
  images. See: https://github.com/docker-hardened-images/catalog
- This Apache 2.0 grant covers Docker's DHI definitions only. The software
  packages inside the image retain their own upstream licenses, including:
    * Amazon Corretto (OpenJDK) — GNU General Public License v2 with the
      Classpath Exception
    * GNU C Library (glibc) — GNU Lesser General Public License
    * Debian base packages — their respective upstream licenses
- Docker publishes a per-image Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) for the exact
  package set and versions in each DHI tag, via the catalog at
  https://hub.docker.com/hardened-images/catalog/dhi/amazoncorretto

Modifications by Innovar Healthcare: this image adds the BridgeLink runtime under
/opt/bridgelink, a shell-free Java bootstrap launcher (bootstrap/), and runs as
the non-root user UID 65532. It does not modify the base OS or JDK packages.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Rocky Linux image (Dockerfile) is unaffected by the above and is built FROM
rockylinux:9 with OpenJDK 17 installed via the distribution package manager.

